              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8998226005721387983">Two stories that undoubtedly deserve the title of &quot;classic&quot;. Wells proves how far ahead of his age he actually was with the way he shapes his pessimistic, socialist outlook on the future of human existence into two narratives of extreme scientific thinking and moral inquiries. Fascinating to read, intriguing how he could so fully conceive such concepts in the late Victorian Age.</span>
  <span id="freeText8998226005721387983" style="display:none">Two stories that undoubtedly deserve the title of "classic". Wells proves how far ahead of his age he actually was with the way he shapes his pessimistic, socialist outlook on the future of human existence into two narratives of extreme scientific thinking and moral inquiries. Fascinating to read, intriguing how he could so fully conceive such concepts in the late Victorian Age.</span>
